HEADWORD: Conduplicate
<hw>Con*du"pli*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>conduplicatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>conduplicare</ets>. See
<er>Duplicate</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Folded lengthwise
along the midrib, the upper face being within; -- said of leaves or
petals in vernation or ⟦ae⟧stivation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Conduplication</ent>⟦br⟧
